						<summary>

						<p>On the face of a pillar in the ruined Basava temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 13th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to refer to some charitable act by Banaviseṭṭi, a pious devotee of Guruliṅga-jaṅgama of the Vīraśaiva faith. As the inscription is written in faulty language, it is difficult to make out its import.</p>						

						</summary>
